history.content:
I think you should choose the course you're more interested in. 186 is more work than 168 since 186 has weekly vitamins(not long, but still a task), 5 hws that are basically projects(I think), and 2 midterms vs 1. Nevertheless, you know your schedule best and maybe 186 will be too much.

I took an easy lower-div technical once because it was "less work" than other courses I was interested in, but I became less productive overall. If I had taken a course I liked, the constant studying would be fun and exciting. Instead, I dreaded the short but tedious hws.

Punchline: Less energy, less work probably gets done.

Disclaimer: I'm taking both courses this semester so someone with experience in both can help?

on average, what is the weekly workload of 186 and 168? I understand 168 is on the lighter side, but I would rather take 186. I am enrolled in both, and also taking other challenging technicals so just trying to decide which would be best.
history.subject: workload of 186 and 168
